  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CPiE response focusing on increased awareness raising, PSS and specialized services to conflict-affected children and families in Nangarhar and Kunar provinces, Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Save the Children (SC) will implement a comprehensive package of Child Protection in Emergencies services, including COVID prevention and life saving interventions, in Kunar and Nangarhar Provinces targeting conflict and pandemic affected children and adolescents, internally displaced people and of the host communities (referred to as vulnerable people throughout the proposal). Given the convergence of needs, SC has chosen to target Nurgal, Khas Kunar, Sawkey, Narang and Asad Abad districts, locations in which SC will also implement Education in Emergencies (EiE) programming under another grant, in parallel, as well as Lalpoura, Momandara, Rodat, Ghanikhail districts in Nangarhar.</narrative>
  </description>
